{
  "texts": [
    "The python packages, nltk, contractions, and spaCy were used for processing stop words, contractions, and lemmatization, respectively.",
    "Finally, we extracted a unique occupation for each tweet by matching the unigrams and bigrams of user descriptions to the curated lists of occupations.",
    "Detailed descriptions of the matching steps are included in Appendix B.",
    "Leveraging the identified occupations, we categorized the entire tweet corpus by occupation.",
    "Subsequently, we employed the topics discovered from Section 3.4 to uncover the most prominent topics within each occupation group."
  ]
}